<HL>
   Business Brief -- Maxwell Communication Corp.:
   Berlitz Plans to Sell Stake
   Of 20% in Japanese Unit
</HL>
<DATE>
09/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   BTZ U.MXC
</CO>
<IN>
CONSUMER &amp; HOUSEHOLD SERVICES, LAWN CARE, TAX PREPARATION (CSV)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Berlitz International Inc. said it signed a letter of
intent to sell a 20% stake in its profitable Japanese
subsidiary to Fukutake Publishing Co., a large educational
publishing company in Japan for $25.7 million.
   The companies also agreed to make a public offering in
Japan of the subsidiary "as soon as practicable."
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Berlitz International said proceeds from the sale will be
used to reduce debt and fund an expansion throughout Asia.
Berlitz officials couldn't be reached for further comment.
   Berlitz International is a language instruction company
with 276 schools around the world, 52 of which are in Japan.
The company is 56%-owned by Macmillan Inc., a subsidiary of
Britain's Maxwell Communication Corp.
</TEXT>
